Today I buried my friend. . . 



    today was the hardest day that I've gone through so far in my life so on behalf of the memory of Mike I wanna post one of his favorite songs. . .


I backed my car into a cop car the other day. 
Well he just drove off, sometimes life's OK. 
I ran my mouth off a bit too much, oh what did I say? 
Well you just laughed it off, it was all OK. 

And we'll all float on OK. And we'll all float on OK. 
And we'll all float on OK. And we'll all float on anyway. 

Well, a fake Jamaican took every last dime with that scam. 
It was worth it just to learn some sleight of hand. 
Bad news comes, don't you worry even when it lands. 
Good news will work its way to all them plans. 
We both got fired on exactly the same day. 
Well we'll float on, good news is on the way.

And we'll all float on OK. And we'll all float on OK. 
And we'll all float on OK. And we'll all float on. 
Alright already, we'll all float on. 
No don't you worry. We'll all float on. 
Alright, already. We'll all float on. 
Alright, don't worry. We'll all float on. 

And we'll all float on.
Alright already, we'll all float on.
Alright, don't worry even if things end up a bit too heavy.
We'll all float on.

Alright already, we'll all float on. 
Alright already, we'll all float on OK. 
Don't worry, we'll all float on. 
Even if things get heavy, we'll all float on. 
Alright already, we'll all float on alright. 
Don't you worry, we'll all float on. 
We'll all float on.








 well never forget you mike you'll always be the one in the back of our heads making us laugh when times get hard. we love you.
